<TITLE> ACC sets 13 graft suspects deadline for wealth info </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 28 (bdnews24.com) -- The Anticorruption Commission Thursday asked another 13 people to turn in wealth statements to the graft watchdog by the seven-day deadline from notification. Among them are former BNP ministers barrister Moudud Ahmed and barrister Aminul Haque. Former commerce adviser Barkatullah Bulu and former lawmaker and businessman MA Hashem also appear on the list. ACC chairman Hasan Mashhud Chowdhury said: "There are hundreds of others on the ACC list." "The commission will notify all of them in phases. Anyone who has allegations of corruption has to submit wealth statements," he said. bdnews
